sequenceDiagram
  autonumber
  participant User as Institution User
  participant IdP as Enterprise IdP
  participant IG as Platform API Gateway
  participant ITS as Identity/Tenant Service
  participant WF as Workflow Engine
  participant CG as Connector Gateway
  participant Down as Downstream Service

  User->>IdP: Authenticate (OIDC/SAML)
  IdP-->>User: ID token / auth code
  User->>IG: API request with access token
  IG->>ITS: Validate token, resolve tenant and roles
  ITS-->>IG: Auth context {tenant_id, org_id, user_id, roles}
  IG->>WF: Forward request with tenant context and trace_id

  WF->>CG: Invoke connector action with workflow context
  CG->>ITS: Request short-lived service token (scoped)
  ITS-->>CG: Service token {tenant_id, workflow_run_id, policy_hash}
  CG->>Down: Call downstream API with mapped auth
  Down-->>CG: Response payload
  CG-->>WF: Normalized response + contract envelope

  WF->>IG: Return API response
  IG-->>User: Response with trace_id

  Note over ITS,CG: Tenant boundary enforced at policy + token issuance
  Note over WF,CG: All calls carry trace_id and workflow_run_id
